[
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609742",
        "quote": "The moral values, ethical codes and laws that guide our choices in normal times are, if anything, even more important to help us navigate the confusing and disorienting time of a disaster.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609742"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Normal",
                "url": "/topics/normal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Navigate",
                "url": "/topics/navigate"
            },
            {
                "name": "Codes",
                "url": "/topics/codes"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609741",
        "quote": "If you ever face a significant disaster, do your best to keep up the spirits of those around you, act flexibly and creatively to help, try to sort rumors from truth, and remember that the decisions you make will have repercussions after the disaster has passed.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609741"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Best",
                "url": "/topics/best"
            },
            {
                "name": "Rumors",
                "url": "/topics/rumors"
            },
            {
                "name": "Repercussions",
                "url": "/topics/repercussions"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609738",
        "quote": "The threat from extreme weather events highlights the importance of investing in preparedness.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609738"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Highlights",
                "url": "/topics/highlights"
            },
            {
                "name": "Preparedness",
                "url": "/topics/preparedness"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609730",
        "quote": "It is human nature to be shortsighted and to lose momentum to make changes once the story is out of the headlines and there aren't financial incentives or political rewards. We owe to ourselves to learn from the past so we can try to do better.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609730"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Financial",
                "url": "/topics/financial"
            },
            {
                "name": "Shortsighted",
                "url": "/topics/shortsighted"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609734",
        "quote": "While Hurricane Katrina demonstrated the dangers of failing to evacuate hospitals from the path of a storm, Hurricane Gustav demonstrated that moving thousands of sick people has its own risks. Gustav also highlighted a critical vulnerability of American hospitals - an inability to withstand prolonged blackouts.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609734"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Critical",
                "url": "/topics/critical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hospitals",
                "url": "/topics/hospitals"
            },
            {
                "name": "Dangers",
                "url": "/topics/dangers"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609733",
        "quote": "The journalistic code of ethics governing the broadcasts requires that opposing views be presented, and that journalists' personal opinions or judgments be left out of factual reporting.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609733"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Code",
                "url": "/topics/code"
            },
            {
                "name": "Journalistic",
                "url": "/topics/journalistic"
            },
            {
                "name": "Opposing",
                "url": "/topics/opposing"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609727",
        "quote": "Ever since Katrina, there has been a proliferation of efforts at the state level and among hospital administrators to come up with guidelines that would help professionals stuck in a situation like this to prioritize patients. These are questions of values much more than they are of medicine or nursing. They're the province of everybody.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609727"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Values",
                "url": "/topics/values"
            },
            {
                "name": "Everybody",
                "url": "/topics/everybody"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609728",
        "quote": "Before journalism, I had worked doing medical aid work in conflict zones. Then, as a journalist, I had written about hospitals in war zones.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609728"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Doing",
                "url": "/topics/doing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hospitals",
                "url": "/topics/hospitals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609729",
        "quote": "Having worked in disasters, I have seen that, in those critical first few hours, those first few days - so much ends up riding on you and your neighbor and whoever is around. The official response always comes later, and it always feels like it comes too slow.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609729"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Critical",
                "url": "/topics/critical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Feels",
                "url": "/topics/feels"
            },
            {
                "name": "Official",
                "url": "/topics/official"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609731",
        "quote": "There are places in the world that the power goes out in hospitals, and there isn't clean water, and it's horrific.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609731"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Places",
                "url": "/topics/places"
            },
            {
                "name": "Horrific",
                "url": "/topics/horrific"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hospitals",
                "url": "/topics/hospitals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609732",
        "quote": "There is a tomorrow after a disaster, and it's sometimes hard to remember that in the midst of it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609732"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Remember",
                "url": "/topics/remember"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sometimes",
                "url": "/topics/sometimes"
            },
            {
                "name": "Midst",
                "url": "/topics/midst"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609735",
        "quote": "When Katrina struck in 2005, roughly 300 deaths were recorded at hospitals, long-term care facilities and in nursing homes, according to a recently published study of death certificates and disaster mortuary team records. Many of them might have been saved if they had been evacuated sooner.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609735"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Study",
                "url": "/topics/study"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Hospitals",
                "url": "/topics/hospitals"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609736",
        "quote": "In the United States, Western Europe and Japan, there is widespread access to dialysis, most of it publicly funded. But in many countries, the majority of patients who need dialysis die without it.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609736"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Die",
                "url": "/topics/die"
            },
            {
                "name": "United States",
                "url": "/topics/united_states"
            },
            {
                "name": "Access",
                "url": "/topics/access"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609737",
        "quote": "A patient healthy enough to undergo a kidney transplant might someday no longer need dialysis. That would free up a slot for a new patient.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609737"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New",
                "url": "/topics/new"
            },
            {
                "name": "Need",
                "url": "/topics/need"
            },
            {
                "name": "Might",
                "url": "/topics/might"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609739",
        "quote": "It remains to be seen the extent to which the critical needs of seniors in low income high rises, people with home medical needs and those with disabilities have been adequately planned for and met during widespread power outages. I fear the answers.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609739"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Medical",
                "url": "/topics/medical"
            },
            {
                "name": "Income",
                "url": "/topics/income"
            },
            {
                "name": "Extent",
                "url": "/topics/extent"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609740",
        "quote": "Be an advocate for your loved ones in the hospital. Ask tough questions of your local hospital and health system about preparedness for the likeliest emergencies, and express your views on how medical resources should be allocated in case they ever fall short.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Sheri Fink",
            "url": "/quotes/sheri_fink_609740"
        },
